    <details>
        <description>
	    Rather than just relying of the feedback from tutors, students review and provide feedback on
	    each other's work. This not only increases the range and volume of feedback each student gains,
	    but gives all student visibility of the range of possible outcomes/solutions produced by others.
	</description>
        <applicability>
	    Can work in a wide variety of contexts for a range of different assignments.
	</applicability>
        <consequences>
	    Due to the cross-visibility of work, this can result in competition and even arguments between students.
	    Quality, accuracy and impartiality of the recieved feedback may be variable.
	</consequences>
    </details>
    
